      <p>Paddling is the most underrated skill in surfing. While everyone focuses on riding waves, the reality is that you'll spend 80% of your session paddling. Most surfers struggle with inefficient technique that burns energy and leads to shoulder injuries. The key to better surfing isn't just catching wavesâ€”it's getting to the lineup efficiently and having energy left to actually surf.</p>
      
