    <section class="body-positioning">
      <h2>Finding Your Sweet Spot</h2>
      <p>Your body position on the board is crucial for efficient paddling. Most surfers lie too far back, which creates drag and makes paddling feel like pushing a boulder. The optimal position varies by board type, but the principle is the same: you want your board to plane, not plow.</p>
      
      <p>Start by lying with your chest just behind the center of the board. Your chin should be up, looking forward, not down at the board. This position allows your shoulders to rotate freely and your arms to reach forward without strain. Your legs should be together and relaxedâ€”no kicking, no tension.</p>
      
