    <section class="breathing-rhythm">
      <h2>The Breathing Connection</h2>
      <p>Your breathing pattern directly affects your paddling efficiency. Most surfers hold their breath or breathe shallowly, which creates tension and reduces power. The key is to establish a rhythm that matches your stroke rate.</p>
      
      <p>Try this: breathe in as your hand enters the water, and breathe out as you pull through. This creates a natural rhythm that keeps you relaxed and powerful. Don't force itâ€”let your body find its natural cadence. The goal is to paddle at a pace you can maintain for 20 minutes without feeling winded.</p>
      
