    <section class="duck-diving-mastery">
      <h2>Mastering the Duck Dive</h2>
      <p>Duck diving is where most surfers waste energy. They either try to muscle through waves or bail and get pushed back. The key is timing and technique, not strength.</p>
      
      <p>Start your duck dive earlier than you think. As the wave approaches, push down on the nose of your board with one hand while using your knee to push the tail down. The goal is to get the entire board under the wave, not just part of it. Your body should follow the board down, not fight against it.</p>
      
      <p>The most common mistake is trying to duck dive too late. By the time the wave is breaking on you, it's too late. Start the motion when the wave is still 10-15 feet away. This gives you time to get deep enough to avoid the full force of the white water.</p>
      
