    <section class="reading-the-ocean">
      <h2>Reading the Ocean</h2>
      <p>Efficient paddling isn't just about techniqueâ€”it's about strategy. Smart surfers use the ocean's energy instead of fighting it. This means understanding rip currents, wave patterns, and timing your paddling to work with the ocean, not against it.</p>
      
      <p>Look for rip currents when paddling out. These are your friends, not enemies. A rip current can cut your paddle-out time in half if you use it correctly. Paddle parallel to the beach until you find a rip, then let it carry you out past the breakers.</p>
      
      <p>When positioning for waves, think about energy conservation. Don't paddle frantically back and forth. Find a spot where you can catch waves without excessive paddling, and stay there. The best surfers are the ones who move the least.</p>
      
